=head1 DESCRIPTION

A custom grouping of objects that include filters for prefixes,
suffixes, object tags, object size, or object age. You can create an S3
Storage Lens group that includes a single filter or multiple filter
conditions. To specify multiple filter conditions, you use C<AND> or
C<OR> logical operators.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Filter => L<Paws::S3Control::StorageLensGroupFilter>

Sets the criteria for the Storage Lens group data that is displayed.
For multiple filter conditions, the C<AND> or C<OR> logical operator is
used.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Name => Str

Contains the name of the Storage Lens group.


=head2 StorageLensGroupArn => Str

Contains the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Storage Lens group. This
property is read-only.



